2026-03-03 Update – Created Enforceable Spec-Kit Constitution:
- Read `README.md` to anchor constitution rules to product intent (deterministic DSL + constrained repair + Playwright execution).
- Added `speckit/constitution.md` with enforceable `MUST`/`MUST NOT` governance, architecture, security, and PR quality gates.
- Defined required modular testing model:
  - Atomic reusable test steps with explicit `inputs/outputs/preconditions/postconditions`.
  - Regression suites execute chainable `test modules`, not isolated tests.
  - Explicit step-to-step state passing (auth/session/user context) is required.
  - Browser/session reuse across chained steps is allowed when documented.
- Added completion and anti-scope rules to discourage non-task work unless an approved spec-kit task exists.

2026-03-03 Update – Constitution Amendment (Version Control Rules):
- Added `Version Control Discipline` section to `speckit/constitution.md`.
- Enforced branch-only development and prohibition of direct commits to `main`.
- Enforced requirement that all task branches merge back to `main`.
- Enforced clean-`main` precondition before creating a new branch (`git status` must be clean).
- Added branch hygiene rule requiring one branch per approved spec-kit task with no unrelated scope.

