2026-03-03 Update – TellGovernment First Login Test:
- On branch `task/tellgovernment-testing-foundation`, updated login smoke plan at `projects/tellgovernment.com/plans/login-smoke.plan.json` to validate TellGovernment.us login success.
- Changed entry URL from `https://app.tellgovernment.com` to `https://tellgovernment.us`.
- Replaced non-validating timeout step with explicit success assertion:
  - `expect urlIncludes="/officials" timeoutMs=15000`
- Added authenticated content assertion:
  - `expect textVisible="Donald Trump" timeoutMs=15000`
- Stored provided test credentials in local ignored file:
  - `projects/tellgovernment.com/test-user.env.local`
  - Keys: `TELLGOV_USERNAME`, `TELLGOV_PASSWORD`
- Validation run:
  - `node packages/cli/dist/index.js run projects/tellgovernment.com/plans/login-smoke.plan.json --env projects/tellgovernment.com/test-user.env.local --dry-run`
  - Result: passed, runIds `run_1772552564944`, `run_1772552688633`
- Live (non-dry-run) execution results:
  - Run `run_1772552750349` failed at step 1 due DNS resolution (`https://tellgovernment.us` -> `ERR_NAME_NOT_RESOLVED`).
  - Updated plan base URL back to `https://app.tellgovernment.com`.
  - Run `run_1772552804397` then passed login + `/officials` URL assertion and failed only content assertion:
    - Expected `textVisible="Donald Trump"` not found within timeout.
    - Failure DOM indicates officials page includes `Donald J. Trump`.
  - After plan update, run `run_1772553051601` passed all steps.
- Completion decision:
  - Marked TellGovernment login smoke test task complete.
  - Acceptance validated in live run: successful login, `/officials` route reached, and expected officials-page content assertion passed.

2026-03-03 Update – Settings Address Toggle Test (MA <-> TX):
- Added new plan: `projects/tellgovernment.com/plans/settings-address-toggle.plan.json`.
- Test flow:
  - Login as existing test user.
  - Open `Settings` from profile menu.
  - Update address fields to MA target and save.
  - Assert return to `/officials` and `Massachusetts` visible.
  - Reopen `Settings`, update to TX target and save.
  - Assert return to `/officials` and `Texas` visible.
- Validation runs:
  - Dry-run passed: `run_1772555727588`.
  - Live run `run_1772555738275` failed because settings modal stayed open after save and intercepted profile-menu click.
  - Updated plan to click `Close` after each save.
  - Live run `run_1772555766769` then progressed through second save, but final assertion failed:
    - `Texas` not visible within timeout.
    - Failure DOM shows officials context remained `Woods Hole, MA` (Massachusetts tabs still present).
- Decision:
  - Keep current strict `Texas` assertion to surface this behavior as a failing regression signal until address-state switching to TX is confirmed working.

2026-03-03 Update – Settings Save Debug Root Cause:
- Investigated settings flow in live Playwright probes to isolate why modal did not close and TX assertion failed.
- Observed behavior:
  - `Save Changes` keeps the settings modal open in automation sessions for this user.
  - Reopening settings after save reverts to persisted MA profile values (`232 Quissett Avenue`, `Woods Hole`, `MA`, `02543`).
  - Location banner remains `Showing officials for Woods Hole, MA`.
- Captured network on save:
  - Request: `PUT https://app.tellgovernment.com/api/profiles/<userId>`
  - Response: `500`
  - Body: `{\"error\":\"Address change rate limited. Please try again in 24 hours.\"}`
- Conclusion:
  - Primary blocker is backend rate limiting on address changes for current test user, not a test-runner click failure.

2026-03-03 Update – Added Rate-Limit Handling Test:
- Added plan `projects/tellgovernment.com/plans/settings-address-rate-limit-close.plan.json`.
